{
  "texts": [
    "Our observation that human-labeled medical advice was not perceived as significantly more comprehensible than AI-labeled information indicates that the label effect exerted less influence on this dimension compared to factors such as reliability and empathy.",
    "Possibly, this",
    "3.0 3.5 4.0 4.5 Empathy Reliability Comprehensibility Willingness Rating ± SE Human (n = 410) AI (n = 410) Human + AI (n = 410)",
    "dimension was perceived more technical in nature and therefore less critical for sensitive medical settings.",
    "In this respect, AI could therefore perform on an equivalent level with human physicians."
  ]
}